  "prompt": "Which method is better, designing in Photoshop or HTML/CSS?",
  "response": "Both Photoshop and HTML/CSS have their strengths, and the best method depends on the specific project and design goals:\n\nPhotoshop Advantages:\n- Precise visual design\n- Advanced graphic manipulation\n- Complete creative freedom\n- Better for complex visual effects\n- Ideal for mockups and concept designs\n\nHTML/CSS Advantages:\n- Direct implementation\n- Responsive design\n- Faster iteration\n- Real-time browser preview\n- Better for web-specific layouts\n- More cost-effective\n- Easier to make responsive\n\nRecommended Approach:\n1. Create initial concept in Photoshop\n2. Translate design to HTML/CSS\n3. Refine directly in code\n4. Use design tools like Figma for modern design workflows\n\nModern Trend:\nMany designers now prefer tools like:\n- Figma\n- Sketch\n- Adobe XD\n- Webflow\n\nThese combine visual design with code-like precision and responsive capabilities.\n\nBest Practice:\nUse a combination of tools based on project requirements and personal workflow.",
